Your guild did a terrible thing, Wulf, and snideness aimed at myself cannot clear the air.  Lets be clear what we are talking about, here.  <br>
<br>
Your guild, led by the Leader of the Legion of Little Folk, Gotrik, pushed into Fear minutes before the Fed-scheduled raid on the plane.  Steely, the raidleader, pled with Gotrik in tells to please stop what he was doing, and asked Gotrik why he was going into Fear when the Fed had a raid scheduled that day at that time?  Gotrik told him that Legion had a wizard who needed his epic.  Steely again pled with Gotrik, informed him that the Fed had a wizard who had signed up to the raid posted on the boards and also needed the drop, and told Gotrik that on his raid everyone had a fair chance to roll on the drop. He asked Gotrik why no Legion signed up to his raid if they needed a drop from the zone?  Gotrik did not respond.<br>
<br>
Steely then sent tells to Faendrill, the voice of the Federation, who he says tried also to persuade Legion from usurping the previously scheduled raid.  Faendrill has not responded on any thread on this topic so I cannot know the contents of that discussion.<br>
<br>
What I can know is that Gotrik, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>the leader of the Legion of Little Folk</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, ignored Steely's pleas and took Feppsi, Zabbena, Ikipu, Ravilicus - <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>ALL officers of Legion of Little Folk</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - and Deanne, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>the leader of Legion of Other Folk</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> into the zone and killed the golem.  Then Voridian, another officer of Legion of Other Folk, looted the item. <br>
<br>
An hour after Steely asked Gotrik to stop, Gotrik then invited Steely back into the zone.  Of course, disheartened and defeated, Steely's band of Federation had already dispersed. <br>
<br>
What I can also know is that your response to his whole affair, something that I think has broken every guild's trust in both Legion and the Federation, is to ridicule me and this post.  But you cannot and you should not make light of Legion's betrayal.  Your are the First Officer of Legion of Other Folk.  You should be ashamed, as should every member of both Legion guilds, for the acts of their Leaders and the acts of their Officers.  Nothing in game is worth trampling the ideals of this alliance.  Nothing can be said that will clear the air here.  Steely/Tanadin, is a young man who had posted the first real Federation raid in months led by one of the smallest guilds in this alliance, SoTR.  Amazingly, he got together a strong enough band of Federation members from the ranks of the other small guilds in this alliance (for few of the large alliance guilds were willing to support his raid).  This raid was what the Federation used to stand for. <br>
<br>
Ridicule me, if you like.  Make fun of me, if it makes you feel better.  But apologize to the Federation for ignoring its existence for months on end and then breaking its trust, breaking the back of what Kulina and Lachadan tried to build, in a single day through the actions of your chosen guild leaders.  <br>
<br>
You think that is funny?  You think comments of Kleenex and snide woodelf speak are humorous?  Thank you, First Officer of the Legion of Other Folk, for your compassion and concern.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000060><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/bfederationofpovar.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eddster2>Eddster2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>General of the Federation<BR>(Master Raid Leader)</span><br>  Posts: 204<br> <font color=#70DB93>(1/14/03 12:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /agree</span><hr size=1> I apologize for taking down Broken Golem after having found out a fed raid was planned. It was not my intention to usurp a raid, and i did not know that i was when i entered fear.<br>
