<br>
Now, this could be seen as a big slight on our part...not following Fed raids closely, etc.  but alot of us play very spontaneously these days.  We don't do many sign-up raids anymore because most everything we do is based on mob availability and who we have available to participate.  Most of us can commit to raiding no more than once a week, and usually that time is reserved for guild raids.<br>
<br>
I am sorry that people feel slighted by what happened.<br>
<br>
I apologize to Jasy, and whoever else may have had an interest in the Enraged Golem.  I hope they can appreciate the time, patience, and effort Voridian has put into completing his epic...this was the last piece he has needed for AGES, and he has cancelled his plans to get guild support in taking down the golem spawn in the past because he caught wind of the Fed mobilizing, or doing a raid.  I am CERTAIN that it was NOT his intention to &quot;steal the kill&quot; from anybody.<br>
<br>
We broke the plane with 2 groups of high level folks using AE.<br>
<br>
Gotrik was informed while we were in Fear of the Fed raid, but it wasn't planned to begin for hours and we were already in the thick of clearing to the Golem.  Most of us were going to log off immediately after getting the BG for Voridian.<br>
<br>
